function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(w -> isuppercase(w[1]), words)
end
```

This function filters the input list `words` and keeps only the elements `w` for which the first character `w[1]` is uppercase, using the `isuppercase` function. The `filter` function creates a new collection containing only the elements that satisfy the given predicate.
